          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(37,99,235,0.1);color:var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Keep tooltip text concise &#8212; 1&#8211;2 short sentences maximum.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Show Icon=OFF</code> when the icon is redundant with the trigger icon.</li>
                <li>Set the correct <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Position</code> so the arrow always points at the trigger.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">RTL=true</code> for Arabic/Hebrew content.</li>
                <li>Dismiss on <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Escape</code> and when focus leaves the trigger.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Use a tooltip to display data tables, images, or interactive elements.</li>
                <li>Show the icon when it adds no meaning beyond the text.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">without arrow</code> in contexts where the tooltip appears far from the trigger.</li>
                <li>Use the LTR label for RTL text &#8212; it will be left-aligned and feel incorrect.</li>
                <li>Keep the tooltip visible after the user interacts with another element.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
