          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="choosing-a-theme" class="doc-section-title">Choosing a Theme</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Match the tooltip theme to the surrounding UI surface.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Theme</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>General informational context on a light UI surface</td><td><code>dark</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>UI surface is dark or mid-tone (e.g. dark sidebar, header)</td><td><code>light</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Explaining an error, destructive action, or blocked state</td><td><code>red</code></td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="choosing-a-position" class="doc-section-title">Choosing a Position</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Position guidance for common trigger placements.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Prefer <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">up center</code> or <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">down center</code> for most inline triggers &#8212; they are the most predictable.</li>
              <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">right</code> or <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">left</code> when the trigger is at the top/bottom edge of the viewport.</li>
              <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">without arrow</code> only when the tooltip is positioned by a layout constraint and the visual connection to the trigger is already clear.</li>
              <li>Avoid <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">up left</code> / <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">up right</code> unless you need to anchor to a specific corner of a wide trigger.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective Tooltip usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li>Keep tooltip text concise &#8212; 1&#8211;2 short sentences maximum.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Show Icon=OFF</code> when the icon is redundant with the trigger icon.</li>
                <li>Set the correct <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Position</code> so the arrow always points at the trigger.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">RTL=true</code> for Arabic/Hebrew content.</li>
                <li>Dismiss on <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Escape</code> and when focus leaves the trigger.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li>Use a tooltip to display data tables, images, or interactive elements.</li>
                <li>Show the icon when it adds no meaning beyond the text.</li>
                <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">without arrow</code> in contexts where the tooltip appears far from the trigger.</li>
                <li>Use the LTR label for RTL text &#8212; it will be left-aligned and feel incorrect.</li>
                <li>Keep the tooltip visible after the user interacts with another element.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="rtl-support" class="doc-section-title">RTL Support</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">When RTL=true, the tooltip renders Arabic text right-aligned. The icon remains on the left of the layout direction.</p>
            <div class="demo-container" style="margin-top:24px;">
              <div class="demo-toolbar"><div class="demo-theme-pill">RTL Preview</div></div>
              <div class="demo-canvas" style="min-height:140px;">
                <div class="tt-demo">
                  <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;">
                    <div class="tt-arrow left dark" style="position:static;margin-right:-1px;"></div>
                    <div class="tt-body dark" dir="rtl">
                      <span>&#x647;&#x630;&#x627; &#x62A;&#x644;&#x645;&#x64A;&#x62D; &#x645;&#x641;&#x64A;&#x62F; &#x64A;&#x648;&#x641;&#x631; &#x633;&#x64A;&#x627;&#x642;&#x64B;&#x627; &#x625;&#x636;&#x627;&#x641;&#x64A;&#x64B;&#x627; &#x62D;&#x648;&#x644; &#x647;&#x630;&#x627; &#x627;&#x644;&#x639;&#x646;&#x635;&#x631;</span>
                      <svg class="tt-icon" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M10 9v4M10 7h.01" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
