        <!-- ========== ACCESSIBILITY ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-accessibility" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <h2 id="accessibility" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for ensuring Tooltip is accessible across assistive technologies and input methods.</p>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="keyboard-interaction" class="doc-h3">Keyboard Interaction</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Trigger</th><th>Tooltip Action</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>Tab</code> / focus enters the trigger</td><td>Tooltip appears</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Escape</code></td><td>Tooltip dismisses immediately</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Focus leaves trigger (blur)</td><td>Tooltip dismisses with delay (300ms recommended)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Hover on trigger</td><td>Tooltip appears (200ms delay recommended)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Hover leaves trigger</td><td>Tooltip dismisses (150ms delay recommended)</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:16px 20px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.15);border-radius:12px;">
              <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Tooltips triggered by hover <strong>must also</strong> be triggerable by keyboard focus &#8212; they are not mutually exclusive.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="aria-attributes" class="doc-h3">ARIA Attributes &amp; Screen Reader Guidance</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Role:</strong> Always use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">role="tooltip"</code> on the tooltip container.</li>
              <li><strong>Association:</strong> Connect trigger to tooltip via <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-describedby="[tooltip-id]"</code>. Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label</code> or <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-labelledby</code> on the trigger if it has no visible text.</li>
              <li><strong>Hidden state:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-hidden="true"</code> when the tooltip is not visible; <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">"false"</code> when shown.</li>
              <li><strong>Keyboard trigger:</strong> Tooltip must appear on <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">:focus</code> &#8212; not hover only.</li>
              <li><strong>Escape:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Escape</code> key must dismiss the tooltip without moving focus.</li>
              <li><strong>Persistent on hover:</strong> The tooltip itself must be hoverable (pointer-events) so users can copy text or reach a scrollbar.</li>
              <li><strong>RTL:</strong> Set <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">dir="rtl"</code> on the tooltip container (or a parent) for Arabic/Hebrew content.</li>
              <li><strong>Icon:</strong> Icon must be <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-hidden="true"</code> &#8212; the text already conveys the full meaning.</li>
              <li><strong>No interactive content:</strong> Do not place buttons, links, or inputs inside a <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">role="tooltip"</code> &#8212; use a Popover for interactive overlays.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="focus-state-design" class="doc-h3">Focus State</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Visible focus indicator:</strong> The trigger element that activates the tooltip must have a clearly visible focus ring (WCAG 2.4.7).</li>
              <li><strong>Focus does not auto-move:</strong> When the tooltip appears, focus stays on the trigger element. The tooltip is not focusable itself.</li>
              <li><strong>Escape behavior:</strong> Pressing <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">Escape</code> dismisses the tooltip without moving focus away from the trigger.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
